name: v2.7
body: - Allow list on top of header

name: v2.6
body:
Thanks for everyone who waited patiently for this release. This is a release filled with pull request contributions.

Fixes include:
- Fixes memory leak
- Fixes layout issues
- Adds delegate methods

name: v2.5.2
body: - Add method to block child layout

name: v2.5.0
body:
- ExpandableStickyListHeaderListView, expand and collaps groups with each group having a sticky header.
- Add multiple new delegate methods for underlying list view
- Allow for negative StickyHeaderTopOffset

name: v2.4.1
body: Fix issue which caused header to sometimes not disappear correctly when at the top of the list

name: v2.4.0
body: - Added ability to set a sticky header offset. This makes SLH work great in combination with transparent actionbars.

name: v2.3.0
body: Lots of minor bug fixes, check issues closed for more details

name: v2.2.0
body:
- Make setOnTouchListener() work as expected
- Stop drawing headers when list is empty

name: v2.1.0
body: A lot of bugs from 2.0 fixed

name: Return of the header
body: Totally re-written header management. No longer subclasses ListView to increase stability and maintainability
